{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"content":["Place 3 peppercorns, 2 allspice berries, and 2 cloves into each of 4 mason jars (1 pint ea.) and set aside.","Place vinegar, water, sugar, salt, oregano, fennel and mustard seeds into mixing bowl and cook <nobr>12 min\/212°F\/speed 2<\/nobr>.","Add cauliflower, carrots, red pepper, green olives, pearl onions, celery, garlic and chili and cook <nobr>7 min\/212°F\/\/speed <\/nobr>. Using a slotted spoon, evenly divide vegetables into reserved mason jars.","Pour the hot brine into each jar and fill, leaving ¼ inch headspace. Clean rim of jars with a damp paper towel and top with lid.  Let cool to room temperature, then refrigerate for 2 days before serving or package for gift giving."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"","content":["12 black peppercorns","8 whole allspice berries","8 whole cloves","24 oz white wine vinegar","12 oz water","3 oz sugar","1 tbsp kosher salt","1 tsp dried oregano","1 tsp fennel seeds","1 tsp mustard seeds","14 oz cauliflower, small florets","6 oz carrots, sliced on the bias (¼ in.)","6 oz red bell pepper, julienned (¼ in.)","4 oz green olives, pitted","6 oz pearl onions, trimmed and peeled","3 oz celery, sliced on the bias (½ in.)","4 garlic cloves","12 slices serrano chili, in rings (3 rings per jar)"]}],"id":"r427642","imageLink":"https:\/\/3.bp.blogspot.com\/-Y_DZ9RszG4c\/XZWaFh7mBVI\/AAAAAAAAeWQ\/Yy-de0QDaksWI-7Ucqv0yp4XsqqQkj21gCLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_wzhnY2zWxFJiucHq.png","title":"Giardiniera","publishedAt":"2018-12-07T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"1 g","fat":"1 g","uom":"per 1 portion","carbohydrates":"11 g","calories":"268 kJ \/ 64 kcal"},"usefulItems":"paper towel, mason jars with clap lids (1 pint ea.), refrigerator","hintsAndTricks":["If canning for long-term storage, seal filled jars with lids and rims and prepare a boiling water bath. Boil jars for 10 minutes. Carefully remove jars and allow to sit undistrubed for 24 hours before moving or packaging. Best if consumed within 6 months.","Alternatively, use the oven to sterilize jars. Preheat oven to 225°F. Arrange jars, lids, and bands on cookie sheets. Leave space between each for hot air to circulate. Transfer to preheated oven and allow to \"bake\" for 20 minutes (225°F). Turn off oven and keep oven door closed until ready to can.","Do NOT add cold food to hot jars, or hot food to cold jars.","Allow Giardiniera to marinate in the refrigerator (approx. 2-3 days) before using for full development of flavors."],"basicInfo":["easy","20m","72h 20m","16 portions"]}